      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 40: Removing the `isConnecting(deviceId, channelName)` guard changes duplicate-connection behavior. With `.uniqueName \u003d true`, repeated sync connect calls can use distinct channel names and may no longer be coalesced by the previous `(deviceId, channelName)` in-flight check, potentially creating parallel pending sync connection attempts for the same device. Please either keep an equivalent in-flight guard keyed by device/sync purpose, or document/verify that `connectDevice(..., uniqueName\u003dtrue, forceNewSocket\u003dfalse)` deduplicates pending requests for the same device and connection type.\n\n```suggestion\n    if (connectionManager_.isConnecting(deviceId, channelName)) {\n        JAMI_LOG(\"Already connecting to {}\", deviceId);\n        return;\n    }\n    connectionManager_.connectDevice(deviceId,\n                                     channelName,\n                                     std::move(cb),\n                                     dhtnet::ConnectDeviceOptions {.forceNewSocket \u003d false,\n                                                                   .uniqueName \u003d true,\n                                                                   .connType \u003d \"sync\"});\n```",
